President Joe Biden has announced his intention to nominate Arthur W. Brown as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the Republic of Ecuador. Brown is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and has held various positions in the U.S. Embassy in different countries, including Zimbabwe, Dominican Republic, Nicaragua, Afghanistan, and Democratic Republic of the Congo. He has received several awards for his work in international development and holds an MBA degree from Johns Hopkins University.

